annotationA: Alpha-(1,6)-fucosyltransferase; Catalyzes the addition of fucose in alpha 1-6 linkage to the first GlcNAc residue, next to the peptide chains in N-glycans. The addition is prevented if the GlcNAc residue is already fucosylated
annotationB: GDP-fucose transporter 1; Involved in GDP-fucose import from the cytoplasm into the Golgi lumen. Plays a major role in the fucosylation of N- glycans. Functions redundantly with Efr in the O-fucosylation of Notch, positively regulating Notch signaling
